+## Live runtime certification
+
+P48 owns end-to-end live certification. The distinction is operationally significant because provider authentication, quota, agent routing, the GNHF entrypoint, repository mutation, validation, Git state, and evidence registration can each fail independently after static checks pass.
+
+A certificate requires the real provider-backed route, explicit `-Run`, an actual bounded repository action, focused and broad validators, a coherent commit ahead of the recorded floor, authorized push or PR evidence when applicable, and `.agent-evidence/runtime-certifications/<run_id>/runtime-certification.json`. Anything weaker is a blocker, not partial certification.
